Trailing zeros come from factors of 10, i.e., pairs of (2,5). There are plenty of 2s, so the count is determined by the number of 5s in 42!.

v5(42!) = floor(42/5) + floor(42/25) + floor(42/125) + ... = 8 + 1 + 0 = 9.

\boxed{9}

